headline: UnitedHealth promotes leader of retirement business to replace slain CEO Thompson
summary: UnitedHealth Group will promote one of its top insurance executives to replace Brian Thompson, the slain CEO of its UnitedHealthcare arm.  The company said Thursday that Tim Noel will become the next UnitedHealthcare leader.  Noel most recently led UnitedHealthcare’s Medicare and retirement business.

headline: UnitedHealthcare names new CEO to replace slain Brian Thompson
summary: UnitedHealth Group (UNH) has named company veteran Tim Noel to replace Brian Thompson. Thompson was shot and killed outside a New York City hotel in December. headline: United Health Group names its Medicare chief to take place of slain executive Brian Thompson
summary: UnitedHealth Group (UNH) announced a new chief executive officer for its health insurance unit, UnitedHealthcare, Thursday, filling the role after Brian Thompson was shot to death last month in New York City.

headline: UnitedHealth taps insider to replace slain executive as CEO of insurance unit
summary: Noel will take charge at UnitedHealthcare, the largest U.S. health insurer that provides benefits to more than 50 million Americans, at a critical moment.  The health insurance industry, on the other hand, is grappling with rising costs, driven by increased demand for healthcare under government-backed Medicare plans for older adults or those with disabilities.  UnitedHealth has reported higher-than-expected medical loss ratio - the percentage of premiums spent on medical care - a metric that tracks costs.

headline: US Health Agency CMS To Appeal Medicare Star Ratings Recalculation Ruling
summary: The U.S. health agency, the Centers for Medicare & Medicaid Services (CMS), announced Tuesday that it will appeal a November 2024 ruling to the Fifth Circuit Court of Appeals. What Happened: In October, around 40% of Medicare Advantage plans with prescription drug coverage earned four or more stars in 2025, a decline from this year, according to data released by the CMS. headline: 3 Unstoppable Dividend Stocks That Can Be Pillars to Build Your Portfolio Around

Three stocks that can make for solid investments in your portfolio and generate a ton of dividend income over the years are UnitedHealth Group (NYSE: UNH), Home Depot (NYSE: HD), and Bank of Montreal (NYSE: BMO).
